javac.code

类 Printer

  • java.lang.Object
    • javac.code.Printer
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Symbol.Visitor<java.lang.String,java.util.Locale>, Type.Visitor<java.lang.String,java.util.Locale>
    直接已知子类:
    RichDiagnosticFormatter.RichPrinter

    public abstract class Printer
extends java.lang.Object
implements Type.Visitor<java.lang.String,java.util.Locale>, Symbol.Visitor<java.lang.String,java.util.Locale>
    A combined type/symbol visitor for generating non-trivial localized string representation of types and symbols.

    This is NOT part of any supported API. If you write code that depends on this, you do so at your own risk. This code and its internal interfaces are subject to change or deletion without notice.

      • localize

        protected abstract java.lang.String localize(java.util.Locale locale,
                                             java.lang.String key,
                                             java.lang.Object... args)
        This method should be overriden in order to provide proper i18n support.
        参数:
        locale - the locale in which the string is to be rendered
        key - the key corresponding to the message to be displayed
        args - a list of optional arguments
        返回:
        localized string representation

      • createStandardPrinter

        public static Printer createStandardPrinter(Messages messages)
        Create a printer with default i18n support provided by Messages. By default, captured types ids are generated using hashcode.
        参数:
        messages - Messages class to be used for i18n
        返回:
        printer visitor instance

      • className

        protected java.lang.String className(Type.ClassType t,
                                     boolean longform,
                                     java.util.Locale locale)
        Converts a class name into a (possibly localized) string. Anonymous inner classes get converted into a localized string.
        参数:
        t - the type of the class whose name is to be rendered
        longform - if set, the class' fullname is displayed - if unset the short name is chosen (w/o package)
        locale - the locale in which the string is to be rendered
        返回:
        localized string representation

      • printMethodArgs

        protected java.lang.String printMethodArgs(List<Type> args,
                                           boolean varArgs,
                                           java.util.Locale locale)
        Converts a set of method argument types into their corresponding localized string representation.
        参数:
        args - arguments to be rendered
        varArgs - if true, the last method argument is regarded as a vararg
        locale - the locale in which the string is to be rendered
        返回:
        localized string representation
